# Healthcare Master Data Management (MDM) Pipeline

## Overview

This project demonstrates the implementation of a Healthcare Master Data Management (MDM) framework for managing Healthcare Organization (HCO) and Healthcare Professional (HCP) data using Databricks, PySpark, and SQL.

The solution follows the Medallion Architecture pattern and processes data through Bronze, Silver, and Gold layers to produce trusted master datasets.

---

## Business Problem

Healthcare provider information often exists across multiple systems and sources with inconsistent naming conventions, incomplete attributes, duplicate records, and differing business standards.

Without a centralized MDM process, organizations face challenges such as:

- Duplicate provider records
- Inconsistent reporting
- Poor data quality
- Operational inefficiencies
- Limited visibility across systems

The objective of this project is to establish a trusted provider master by standardizing and validating provider data before publishing it for enterprise use.

---

## Medallion Architecture

### Bronze Layer

Location:

```text
01_Staging
```

Responsibilities:

- Source ingestion
- Raw data storage
- Initial validation
- Incremental loading

Objects:

- STG_HCO
- STG_HCP
- STG_ADDR
- STG_ID

---

### Silver Layer

Location:

```text
02_PreMDM
```

Responsibilities:

- Attribute standardization
- Business rule execution
- Data quality checks
- Address validation
- Data enrichment
- Identifier generation

Objects:

- PREMDM_HCO
- PREMDM_HCP
- PREMDM_ADDR
- PREMDM_ID

---

### Gold Layer

Location:

```text
03_Publish
```

Responsibilities:

- Publishing master records
- Cross-reference generation
- Creation of reporting-ready datasets

Objects:

- PUB_HCO
- PUB_HCP
- PUB_ID
- HCO_XREF
- HCP_XREF

---

## Data Profiling Layer

Location:

```text
00_Profiling
```

Profiling activities include:

- Null analysis
- Duplicate detection
- Attribute completeness analysis
- Data quality assessment
- Distribution analysis

This phase helps identify source system quality issues before ingestion.

---

## Testing Layer

Location:

```text
04_Testing
```

Validation activities include:

- Record count verification
- Business rule validation
- Reconciliation testing
- Data quality verification
- Publishing validation

---

## Databricks Workflow Orchestration

Databricks Workflows are used to automate pipeline execution.

Execution Flow:

```text
STG_ADDR
STG_HCO
STG_HCP
STG_ID
      ↓
ID_GEN
      ↓
PREMDM_ADDR
PREMDM_HCO
PREMDM_HCP
PREMDM_ID
      ↓
PUB_HCP_XREF
PUB_HCO_XREF
      ↓
PUB_HCO
PUB_HCP
PUB_ID
```

This orchestration ensures proper dependency management and scalable processing.

